                    </sizepolicy>
                   </property>
                   <property name="text">
                    <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'MS Shell Dlg 2'; font-size:8pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10pt;&quot;&gt;  After pushing &amp;quot;Start&amp;quot; button program trying to connect controller&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10pt;&quot;&gt;using MUT protocol. In success, program reads calibration &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10pt;&quot;&gt;numbers from controller's memory. By using calibration number, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10pt;&quot;&gt;program searching for xml file in home folder. The name of file &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10pt;&quot;&gt;should include calibrartion number - ROM ID. If xml found, then it &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10pt;&quot;&gt;parses and screen forms tables will be created. The structure of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10pt;&quot;&gt;xml file is identical to xml structure of ECUFLASH with extended &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10pt;&quot;&gt;syntax. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'; font-size:10pt; color:#1d2129;&quot;&gt;In fact, to the description of the table you want to add &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'; font-size:10pt; color:#1d2129;&quot;&gt;RAM_addr parameter address table in RAM (1D tables are not&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'; font-size:10pt; color:#1d2129;&quot;&gt;supported yet). And a separate parameter DEAD_var address &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'; font-size:10pt; color:#1d2129;&quot;&gt;of this variable. I have ready a patch for GTA 80770010 evo &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'; font-size:10pt; color:#1d2129;&quot;&gt;(airtrek) and 90550001 evo7 Ralliart my rom without tephra mod.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'; font-size:10pt; color:#1d2129;&quot;&gt;  After edit cells (select another cell or push enter) value &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'; font-size:10pt; color:#1d2129;&quot;&gt;Immediately send's to ECU. This client worked with two interface,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'; font-size:10pt; color:#1d2129;&quot;&gt; OpenPort1.3 and OpenPort2.0 (slowly). For make patch use &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'; font-size:10pt; color:#1d2129;&quot;&gt;tuner pro from &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.tunerpro.net/downloadApp.htm&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10pt; text-decoration: underline; color:#0000ff;&quot;&gt;http://www.tunerpro.net/downloadApp.htm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'; font-size:10pt; color:#1d2129;&quot;&gt;, and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif'; font-size:10pt; color:#1d2129;&quot;&gt;xdf file.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
